    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160524T153852+0200" comment="Task done by Implmenter, access rights needed." flag="done"?>
    <title><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160509T150134+0200" comment="At next revision, review name of section." flag="done"?>Assign<?oxy_comment_end?>
        names to organisation unit levels</title>
    <?oxy_comment_end?>
    <para>When you add children to an organisation unit, DHIS2 automatically creates a new
        organisation unit level if necessary. The system also assigns a generic name to this level,
        for example "Level 5". You can replace the generic name with a
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160524T155050+0200" comment="At next revision, find a better term." flag="done"?>contextual<?oxy_comment_end?>
        name, for example &quot;Country&quot;,
        &quot;<?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160526T110459+0200" comment="At next revision, define if we should use &quot;&quot; around inline examples or not. 
If so, go trough all topics and update." flag="done"?>Province<?oxy_comment_end?>&quot;,
        &quot;District" or &quot;Health Facility&quot;. DHIS2 uses the contextual names anywhere
        levels are referred to, for example in the <emphasis role="bold">GIS</emphasis> app. </para>
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                    role="bold">Organisation unit</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Organisation
                    unit level</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>The loading time of the list depends on the depth of the organisation unit
                hierarchy tree.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>For the organisation unit levels you want to modify, type a name.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160524T154550+0200" comment="For SME:Do you need to select offline levels? What does Default mean?
E-mail send to Lars 27th May.
Number of levels that are loaded offline, depends on the org unit the user is assigned to. Verify with Lars" flag="done"?>
            <para>Select the number of offline levels.</para>
            <?oxy_comment_end?>
            <note>
                <para>You configure the default value in the <emphasis role="bold">System
                        Settings</emphasis> app:</para>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">System Settings</emphasis> app, click <emphasis
                        role="bold">General</emphasis> and select a level in the <emphasis
                        role="bold">Max offline organisation unit levels</emphasis> list.</para>
            </note>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
</section>
